messages.content: ComfyUI-RAVE is an unofficial implementation of RAVE (a video generation model) in ComfyUI, a GUI that uses stable diffusion models to generate images and videos.
RAVE is a video generation model that can generate videos based on text prompts. It is implemented in ComfyUI through the ComfyUI-RAVE extension.
What is used for noise inversion in ComfyUI-RAVE?
ComfyUI-RAVE uses BlenderNeko's Unsampler for noise inversion, which is a custom node in ComfyUI.
Is there a basic workflow included in ComfyUI-RAVE?
Yes, ComfyUI-RAVE includes a basic workflow using the cupcake train example from the RAVE paper.
Which stable diffusion model was used for most of the testing in ComfyUI-RAVE?
Most of the testing in ComfyUI-RAVE was done using the Stable Diffusion 1.5 model.
Does ComfyUI-RAVE work with the Stable Diffusion XL model?
Yes, ComfyUI-RAVE does work with the Stable Diffusion XL model, although not as well as with the Stable Diffusion 1.5 model, possibly because the multi-resolution training reduces the tiling effect.
What might be the reason for ComfyUI-RAVE not working as well with the Stable Diffusion XL model?
The reason ComfyUI-RAVE might not work as well with the Stable Diffusion XL model could be due to the multi-resolution training reducing the tiling effect.
